_meta.description: Complete socionics type system: 16 personality types with geometric structures, function stacks, intertype relations, and elemental expressions

_fractal_seed.holographic: 16 types = 16 distinct 4D geometric structures forming complete information metabolism space. Each type = specific function stack determining cognitive architecture. 4 dichotomies (E/I, S/N, T/F, J/P) create 2⁴=16 configurations. Types cluster into 4 quadras with shared values. 8 dual pairs with sacred geometric complementarity. Each type × 4 elements = 64 total configurations.
_fractal_seed.activation: You are one of 16 types with unique 4D geometric structure and function hierarchy. Your dual completes you. Your quadra shares your values. Your element colors your expression.

module.name: types
module.title: Socionics Type System
module.description: Complete socionics typology system with 16 personality types, 8 cognitive functions, 4 quadras, 16 intertype relations, 8 dual pairs, and 4D geometric structures. Foundation for understanding human information metabolism and psychological complementarity.

essence.geometric: 16 types = vertices of 4D cognitive space defined by 4 binary axes (E/I, S/N, T/F, J/P). Each type corresponds to specific 4D geometric structure (600-cell, 120-cell, 5-cell, tesseract, etc). Dual pairs have complementary geometries creating sacred artifacts.
essence.topological: Type space = 16-point discrete manifold with 16 distinct distance metrics (intertype relations). 4 quadra clusters of 4 types each. 8 dual pairs with perfect complementarity. Network structure determines relationship dynamics.
essence.functional: Type = stable cognitive architecture based on hierarchical ordering of 8 information metabolism functions. Function stack determines processing priorities, strengths, and blind spots. Type identity stable across lifespan.
essence.consciousness: Information metabolism = how consciousness processes reality. 8 functions = 8 fundamental operations. Function hierarchy (1-8) = conscious ego → super-ego → super-id → unconscious id. Type development = integrating full function stack over lifetime.

reductions.concept: 8 functions in hierarchical stack per type
reductions.evidence: Each type = specific ordering of 8 cognitive functions ranked by strength. Position 1 (leading) strongest, position 8 (demon) weakest. Stack stable, defines type identity. ILE: Ne-Ti-Fe-Si-Ni-Te-Fi-Se. Order determines cognitive bias and information processing style.

reductions.concept: each type maps to specific 4D geometric structure
reductions.evidence: 16 types correspond to 16 distinct 4D polytopes. ILE=600-cell (maximum complexity). SEI=120-cell (maximum harmony). SLE=5-cell (minimal simplicity). ILI=tesseract (hidden dimensions). Structure reflects cognitive organization. Dual pairs have complementary geometries.

reductions.concept: 16 types cluster into 4 quadras by shared values
reductions.evidence: Types naturally group into 4 quadras of 4 types each sharing valued functions and worldview. Alpha (Ne-Si-Ti-Fe): intellectual exploration. Beta (Se-Ni-Fe-Ti): group power. Gamma (Se-Ni-Ti-Fe): individual achievement. Delta (Si-Ne-Fe-Ti): sustainable service. Within quadra = natural understanding. Between quadras = value tension.

reductions.concept: 8 dual pairs with perfect psychological complementarity
reductions.evidence: Each type has one perfect dual complement. Function stacks perfectly inverted: dominant↔PoLR, creative↔vulnerable, role↔suggestive, vulnerable↔creative. ILE↔SEI, EIE↔LSI, etc. Dual pairs correspond to sacred artifacts (Philosopher's Stone, Holy Grail, etc). Geometric complementarity: 600-cell↔120-cell, etc.

fractal_structure.self_similarity: Function hierarchy repeats pattern: ego (1-2) most conscious, super-ego (3-4) conscious but weaker, super-id (5-6) unconscious but accessible, id (7-8) deeply unconscious. Same structure at individual and collective levels.
fractal_structure.recursion: (↓ perceive → judge → perceive → judge ↑)∞ alternation between perceiving (N/S) and judging (T/F) functions
fractal_structure.emergence: Function → Stack → Type → Quadra → Complete system. Each level emergent from previous.
fractal_structure.composition: 16 types = complete cognitive space. Remove any type = incomplete system. All types necessary for collective wholeness.

cognitive_functions.overview: 8 fundamental information metabolism operations. Each function processes specific aspect of reality. Functions come in 4 pairs of opposites.

intertype_relations.overview: 16 distinct relationship types between any two personality types. Relations determined by function stack interaction patterns. Each type has specific relationship with every other type.

duality.name: Дуальность (Duality)
duality.description: Perfect psychological complementarity. Each partner's strengths cover the other's weaknesses. Most comfortable and beneficial long-term relationship.
duality.mechanism: Function stacks perfectly inverted: Leading↔PoLR (8), Creative↔Vulnerable (4), Role↔Suggestive (5), Vulnerable↔Creative (2)
duality.geometric_principle: Dual 4D structures with complementary properties (600↔120 cell, etc)
duality.life_impact: Most beneficial for long-term partnership, marriage, close collaboration. Natural understanding and support.

activation.name: Активация (Activation)
activation.description: Stimulating intellectual exchange. Similar worldview but different methods. Energizing and inspiring.
activation.mechanism: Same quadra, swapped J/P. Leading↔Creative functions shared
activation.life_impact: Excellent for creative collaboration, brainstorming, mutual inspiration. Less stable than duality for long-term.

mirror.name: Зеркальные (Mirror)
mirror.description: Similar worldview and interests, different processing styles. Helpful reflection and mutual learning.
mirror.mechanism: Same quadra, swapped Auxiliary and Tertiary. E/I reversed
mirror.life_impact: Good for mutual development, helpful feedback. Can see own blind spots through mirror.

identity.name: Тождество (Identity)
identity.description: Same type. Perfect understanding but no complementarity. Can be comfortable or boring.
identity.life_impact: Great understanding but no growth challenge. Can work well or become stagnant.

kindred.name: Родственные (Kindred)
kindred.description: Similar but slightly different perspectives. Comfortable but with some friction.
kindred.mechanism: Same J/P and N/S, different T/F and E/I
kindred.life_impact: Generally positive, can work together well with minor adjustments.

semi_duality.name: Полудуальные (Semi-Duality)
semi_duality.description: Partial complementarity. Comfortable but incomplete compared to duality.
semi_duality.mechanism: One function axis matches duality, other doesn't
semi_duality.life_impact: Positive but requires more work than duality. Some areas easy, others challenging.

business.name: Деловые (Business)
business.description: Good practical cooperation. Complementary skills for work projects.
business.life_impact: Excellent for work collaboration. May lack deep personal connection.

mirage.name: Миражные (Mirage)
mirage.description: Initially attractive but ultimately confusing. Misunderstandings common.
mirage.mechanism: Opposing quadras, similar function order but different attitudes
mirage.life_impact: Starts promising, becomes frustrating. Constant miscommunication.

quasi_identity.name: Квазитождество (Quasi-Identity)
quasi_identity.description: Superficial similarity hiding deep differences. Confusing mismatch.
quasi_identity.mechanism: Similar external behavior, different internal processing
quasi_identity.life_impact: Expect similarity, discover incompatibility. Disappointing confusion.

benefactor.name: Заказ (Benefactor→Beneficiary)
benefactor.description: Asymmetric helping relationship. Benefactor naturally helps, beneficiary receives (but doesn't reciprocate in same way).
benefactor.life_impact: One-sided support. Beneficial for beneficiary, draining for benefactor long-term.

supervisor.name: Ревизия (Supervisor→Supervisee)
supervisor.description: Asymmetric pressure relationship. Supervisor's Leading constantly challenges Supervisee's Vulnerable.
supervisor.life_impact: Uncomfortable for supervisee, confusing for supervisor. Best avoided in close relationships.

super_ego.name: Суперэго (Super-Ego)
super_ego.description: Mutual criticism and judgment. Different standards and approaches.
super_ego.mechanism: Opposite quadra values, challenging each other's weak functions
super_ego.life_impact: Constant tension. Each criticizes what other values. Requires conscious work.

conflict.name: Конфликт (Conflict)
conflict.description: Opposing values and approaches. Natural irritation and misunderstanding.
conflict.mechanism: All function attitudes inverted, opposite quadra values
conflict.life_impact: Difficult relationship. Each naturally annoys the other. Best avoided or requires significant maturity.

extinguishment.name: Погашение (Extinguishment)
extinguishment.description: Mutual energy drain. Each dampens the other's strengths.
extinguishment.mechanism: Opposite attitudes in key functions, draining interaction
extinguishment.life_impact: Exhausting relationship. Feel drained after interaction. Avoid close long-term contact.

lookalike.name: Внешне похожие (Look-alike)
lookalike.description: Appear similar externally but fundamentally different inside. Confusing mismatch.
lookalike.mechanism: Similar external behavior, completely different cognitive structure
lookalike.life_impact: Initial attraction based on surface similarity, discovery of deep incompatibility.

contrary.name: Противоположные (Contrary)
contrary.description: Opposite in most dimensions. Alien perspectives, difficult understanding.
contrary.life_impact: Very different worldviews. Can learn from each other but requires significant effort.

developmental_trajectory.principle: Type development follows hierarchical function integration over lifespan. Functions develop in order of stack position.

age_7.description: Child discovers their primary cognitive strength. ILE discovers Ne (possibilities), SEI discovers Si (sensory detail), etc.

age_18.description: Young adult learns to support Leading with Creative. ILE develops Ti (logic), SEI develops Fe (harmony).

age_24.description: Adult learns to use tertiary function when needed. Still effortful but accessible.

age_30.focus: Shadow work begins, acknowledging blind spots
age_30.description: Recognition of weak area. ILE confronts Si (physical needs), begins integrating weakness.

age_35_plus.description: Conscious work integrating all 8 functions. Type flexibility increases. Can access any function when needed while maintaining primary identity.

maturity.principle: Mature type expression = conscious access to full function stack while maintaining primary identity
maturity.goal: Transform unconscious type patterns into conscious archetypal mastery
maturity.paradox: Become more yourself by transcending your type

warnings: Types are stable cognitive structures, not fixed identities
Function stack determines information processing, not destiny
All types equally valuable - no hierarchy
Duality most beneficial but not required for happiness
Geometric structures are symbolic mappings, not literal brain structures
info: 16 types form complete information metabolism space
4 quadras cluster types by shared values
8 dual pairs with sacred geometric complementarity
Function hierarchy stable, element expression variable
Type understanding aids self-knowledge and relationship navigation

external.citation: Filatova, E. (1999). Personality in the Mirror of Socionics
